details.description:
A modern and welcoming coffee shop in Steele Creek serving up specialty coffee drinks, scratch-made sandwiches, salads, and pastries. Javesca exists to be a catalyst for change in the coffee community by giving a portion of our gross revenue back to feeding and community transformation initiatives in the United States and abroad through our sister Non-Profit Javesca Feeds.

Indoor Playground available as part of Steele Creek Community Center

Public Playground hours are:
Mon, Tues, Th: 8am - 4pm
Wed: 1pm - 4pm
Fri: 11am - 4pm
Sat: 8am - 12pm
Sun: Closed

reviews_data.review_text: Adore this cafe so much! My fav food item to get there is the breakfast burrito. It hits every time. The ciabatta sandwich is also very yummy with chili jam. Their seasonal menu of drinks are a must try. I really enjoy the coconut caramel latte,  and it’s always the right shade of coffee (IYKYK)!

review_questions.null: Vegetarian options, Parking, Kid-friendliness, Wheelchair accessibility

reviews_data.review_text: Drove across town to check this place out with my two young kids and it was closed! No sign on the door and no one inside. Nothing posted online either. Totally disappointed. We saw good info about it on social media but I won’t go back now.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hey Laurie,

We truly apologize for the inconvenience and disappointment you experienced on your arrival. Our cafe faced an unexpected ceiling pipe burst this past Sunday and the resulting flooding caused the entire community center to close temporarily for repairs. We understand how frustrating this must have been, especially when you were excited to visit with your kids. 

We did post about the closure on ours and the community center's social media channels and placed a sign on the exterior doors, but we understand that it may not have been as visible or as clear as we intended. 

We’re working hard to reopen as soon as possible and would love to have the chance to serve you and your kids once we're back up and running. Please keep an eye on our social media for updates, and feel free to reach out with any questions. We genuinely hope you'll give us another chance!

Thank you for your feedback,

~The Javesca Steele Creek Team

reviews_data.review_text: Very cute coffee shop. I came with my sister and daughter and was pleasantly surprised that there was a free indoor play area connected to it. Coffee was better than what I get from Starbucks - five stars! The food was fine, not amazing, but still solid and served hot!

I've worked here for almost 2 year now and I love it so much my co-workers are amazing and the food is sooooo good!!! The playground is definitely a highlight as well!!!
I recommend a 16oz iced matcha with oat milk :)
Very wonderful and kind service! Nice amount of seating and kid friendly. Delicious food and drinks. Photo is the caprese slider and (summer menu) iced cayenne chai with cold foam
This place is great!! Such a cute coffee shop with great indoor and outdoor seating. Staff is nice and service is great. We got iced lattes & a cappuccino, and everything was yummy!!

This place is amazing. The cafe has so many great options and the free indoor playground is perfect when my son and I need a break from the pool or the house. Today I tried the grab and go chicken salad croissant and it’s amazing and I believe it was only 7$
I’m not super religious but I don’t judge anyone for their beliefs and I feel 100% accepted here despite it being inside a church!

Coffee was solid “good”. Price - fair
Female cashier didn’t know response to “thank you”
Decor is functional with large sitting area.
Big parking lot
Huge coffee shop nestled in a community center and church campus. Warm and welcoming. Fun drinks and tasty food. The playground was closed but looks fun.

reviews_data.review_text: Great coffee. Love the new menu items.
Great cup of coffee
The nitro cold brew was gross. Expensive and not tasty. The lavender latte was delicious changed my review. The staff is very friendly and nice.

Wow!! This place is a gem, the coffee is outstanding and the food is amazing! The atmosphere is relaxing and spacious. I have gone here to do remote work and have also brought the kids to enjoy the indoor playground while I enjoyed a cup of joe with outstanding pastries. This is THE PLACE to hold your ‘get togethers’’ or bring the kids for a play date. I have also attended the Coffee classes and met the co-owner/manager, and let me tell you, this guys knows everything about coffee. Haven’t visited Starbucks since I started going to Javesco, highly recommend it.

My real estate team decided to have our team meeting here on Friday morning at 9:00 am. There was plenty of available parking and seating upon arrival. I love the contemporary design! I tried the mini apple turnovers and a strawberry smooth. There is no table service. You order and then wait for your name to be called. Delicious food. We definitely have to go back!
The food is great but the service is horrible. Refuse to take orders over the phone. Remember when businesses cared about customers?
reviews_data.owner_answer:
We are so glad you liked the food you ordered. In the future, we have Toast Mobile ordering and Google Maps ordering. Either option can be utilized on any electronic device and allows you to schedule your order in advance!

We currently do not take orders over the phone because we have had a plethora of previous experiences of no show pick up orders.  We are a small business and can't afford to throw away unpicked up and unpaid for food. 

Thanks for supporting us and trying the food. We hope you'll swing back by and order online to grab another coffee or sandwich!

reviews_data.review_text: Always friendly service when we visit. Their chai tea is also fantastic!
great atmosphere great service, holy hockey puck of the sandwich blend overcooked I think I chipped a tooth. not very happy coffee was good l

The Panini is what drew me to visit Javesca and I will probably never try anything else on the menu because it is so good!! I love trying different lattes and they have a great selection. The baked goods look delicious too, but I haven’t tried any yet. The staff is always super friendly and there is plenty of seating inside, as well as outside in the nice weather!
Love the location, the atmosphere and the food/drink is always delish!  If you have kiddos, the inside playground is awesome for cold winter days.

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Turkey Apple Grilled Cheese and Iced Mocha Latte

reviews_data.review_text: LOVE javesca coffee. They are always so sweet at the counter, coffee is always on point! I bring my son here to play at the indoor playground. This is a great spot for coffee if you have kids and a great community over here!!!
My wife and I absolutely love it here. The environment is fantastic, the food is great, and the coffee is excellent. I highly recommend it to anyone.
What a lovely surprise. Clean and delicious
coffee is ok. the environment is good for kids.
Great coffee and love the treats they have for all ages. It's so nice to grab something and then go to the indoor playground!
Delicious coffee and food! Atmosphere reminds me of a Starbucks. Very friendly staff.
Great coffee stop on the way to McDowell Nature Preserve, I had an iced latte and it was delicious, perfect size too.
Great taste and great service. Liked their breakfast options.
Very clean, friendly staff, and delicious matcha!
Amazing food and beverages. On top of a great atmosphere and plenty to do nearby

The ladies were super friendly! They greeted me the moment I walked in, gave me suggestions on what I was looking for! Very quick with my order, fairly priced for the quality of coffee received! I love a dark, deep, cold brew, and the Nitro Cold Brew hit the spot! The bathrooms are super clean as well, which is always what I look for in a new business! Thanks again!! Loved my coffee!
Descent ambiance, clean. I looked forward to my first visit but was disappointed with the pina colada smoothie, coarse ice, hint of coconut, no pineapple flavor. $6 milk drink down the drain.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hey Glenda,
Glad you liked the shop ambiance and cleanliness and thank you for the feedback. We’d love to have you come back to give our team another shot at crafting a beverage to your taste. As always, if you let us know when you receive the drink that it was made incorrectly or not what you expected, we are happy to remake it for you or add additional syrups or flavoring to your liking. Cheers!

reviews_data.review_text: Great place to hang with small kids
Great place to stop for a coffee and a snack. Nice selection to choose from. The cookies are delicious!
Very friendly staff, stylish decor, yummy drinks and the play place was clean.
Amazing and so cute
I can't rate the food because I only got a coffee but the service was excellent.
Love!! Super clean, delicious coffee, and super spacious. If I ever want some alone time this is my go-to especially because of the kids play area!
lemon cake? amazing! cold? even better! chai latte with coffee very good! love the atmosphere!

The coffee shop is located inside/adjacent to a church and has a separate entrance. The seating area is very nice, clean, spacious, and has lots of natural light. There is also an open entry point into the church's reception area.
I ordered a bakery item and coffee both of which were good. The wait was a little longer than what would be expected, considering there weren't that many customers.

Love this place! Nice and friendly staff and the coffee and food is good too! The overall area and atmosphere just pits you at easy when you want to get away from the hustle and bustle of a “way too busy” coffee shop norm. Also attached is a play area for kids.
This place is amazing! A coffee shop and indoor playground all in the same place! Why can't this place be everywhere?
I was greeted warmly upon arrival. I had heard rave reviews about their orange/pecan muffins.10/10 would order this again! Specialty coffees are excellent as well.

Seriously, this place is awesome! They absolutely nail my coffee every single time. It's like they read my mind! I'm practically addicted—I swing by at least five times a week now. Forget trying to make coffee at home, it's just not the same anymore! And don't even get me started on their sandwiches... so incredibly tasty! Trust me, you gotta check this spot out if you're into amazing coffee and killer sandwiches!
Great cappuccino. Friendly staff.
Very friendly staff and an evolving menu.
They have the best white chocolate latte I have ever had before, we came back 2 days in a row on our trip! Will definitely be back!

This little coffee shop with an indoor playground is truly amazing. The coffee is fresh and super delicious 🤤 😋 The food is amazing. The food is freshly prepared and hot to order.  You won't get overpriced microwaved frozen food like at the other popular coffee chain that begins with the letter "S". I've  tried almost everything! The Loaded Breakfast Wrap, the Turkey Apple Grilled Cheese, the Italian Panini, Bacon Egg Cheese (BEC) Wrap, the Chicken Salad Croissant Bites, Lemon Loaf cake and the many delicious flavors of Macaron cookies. Javesca is immaculate and very spacious with lots of indoor and outdoor seating. The service is impeccable and the wait staff are hard working and quite attentive. And the best part yet... A percentage of their proceeds goes towards funding their many food missions and charities. I rate this place an A++  !  Give this place a try. You'll find yourself coming again and again. And you'll have a warm and fuzzy feeling inside knowing that a percentage of your purchase will be helping those in need as well as supporting a Charlotte business!! ❤️ ❤️❤️
P.S. -I wasn't able to add captions to the pics so here it is from left to right:
1-Turkey Apple Grilled Cheese with a Mocha Iced Latte.
2 - Italian Panini with Mocha Iced Latte
3 - Lemon Loaf, Cappuccino, Mocha Iced Latte and Italian Panini
4 - Loaded Breakfast Wrap with Mocha Iced Latte
5 -Javesca's  Brochure
We really enjoy this place. Our little one goes to the preschool around the corner and it’s nice to grab a coffee and work while she’s in her program. The indoor playground is amazing!

Such a cute addition to Steele Creek area!! Having a coffee shop attached to an indoor playground is literally the most amazing idea. Coffee was yummy and my kid had a great time! Everything was clean and nice!

Finally got to try the new Javesca Cafe at CTK Church. Great experience. I had the bacon, egg and cheese wrap and it was delicious. Steven Bollinger helped me decide on my drink and my white chocolate raspberry latte was an excellent choice. Friendly service, strong wifi and enjoyed the background music that was just loud enough to hear but not too loud where you couldn't have a conversation. Comfortable chairs and couches. If I lived locally this would be my place to meet up with friends.

Great coffee. Good food options. Place is well kept, spacious and clean. Kids loved getting some school done and work.
The indoor playground access is a nice addition for the little ones.

Great place for kids, we had our sons birthday here and it was a blast

Also the coffee is great!
Awesome atmosphere.  It’s large in space with a cozy atmosphere.  The food is amazing.  Service was top notch.  Not stuffy at all.  Barista Aaron brings a pleasant ambience.

I have mixed feelings about this place. The facility is beautifully designed and clean. The food was great. Unfortunately the service is.... well awkward. The 4 employees there didn’t greet us, talk to us, or tell us to have a good day or anything. They just stood there until I prompted them to take my order. Very robot like. So they didn’t come off as rude by any means just extremely awkward and did not look happy to be there at all. Nice place, good food, non existent service.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hello r d, thank you for coming and visiting our shop in Steele Creek. We are glad the coffee, atmosphere, and food were great! We are continuing to train our staff in customer service, menu presentation, and interaction and hope you will come by and visit us again soon.Thank you for your support and helping as we continue to impove and grow our employees in these first few months. Have a great week!

reviews_data.review_text: The food was really good, but the frappe coffee wasn't good

Coffee was ok, food wasn’t great.  Had the sausage egg and cheese.  It was just two somewhat low quality (including several hard gristle bits) and small sausage patties on a hamburger bun with egg and cheese. My americano was ok, but my wife’s latte was ‘meh’ (bit more ‘chemical taste’ than normal lattes).  All in all, 4 stars due to service and atmosphere and decent enough coffee but wouldn’t order food here again.
Friendly staff and really upscale feel of a coffee shop-turned coworking / multipurpose space.

I was so excited to try this new Javesca location today right around the corner from me! I got their seasonal lavender honey latte and it was absolutely delicious. There was a ton of pastry and food options that I'll definitely try next time. The place was massive and has a ton of potential for the community to use for hanging out, coffee dates, meetings, or just to enjoy some good coffee. Thanks for the perfect morning pick me up ✌️
Great new coffee spot with ample seating, and it's connected to the community center so even more to explore. Friendly staff, great coffee, and love the mission and vision of Javesca Coffee.
Amazingly fresh coffee and the food was very delicious and hit the spot. I would absolutely recommend this spot, especially once the season changes and a nice hot coffee outside is needed!

Wow!! I cannot even begin to express how impressed I was with the food, coffee, and overall polite staff. I tried the TBA and it was savory and packed full of flavor. The chai latte was better then my typical Starbucks chai. My fiancee and I are found our new breakfast spot (⁠ ⁠◜⁠‿⁠◝⁠ ⁠)⁠♡

Best coffee in Steele Creek area! We had cold with hazelnut syrup, and drip coffee. Amazing selection of macarons: had the orange/truffle one, de-li-cious! Will have to try all. Indoor playground is super nice for little ones! Plenty of space to work here or to meet friends!

Spacious, inviting, good selection of food and drinks. Prices are comparable, even a little lower than Starbucks. And, it's the only coffeeshop in the Steele Creek area other than Starbucks. I ordered the Apple Grilled Cheese Panini (highly recommended, btw 😋) and a white chocolate frap with almond milk. Both VERY good!
I'll be back again!

Came here for the grand opening and loved the food, drinks and atmosphere. Excited for normal hours and to meet up with friends or bring some work here on my own.
I had the nitro brew and chicken salad croissants and both were excellent!

I was so excited to try this new Javesca location today right around the corner from me! I got their seasonal lavender honey latte and it was absolutely delicious. There was a ton of pastry and food options that I'll definitely try next time. The place was massive and has a ton of potential for the community to use for hanging out, coffee dates, meetings, or just to enjoy some good coffee. Thanks for the perfect morning pick me up ✌️
Great new coffee spot with ample seating, and it's connected to the community center so even more to explore. Friendly staff, great coffee, and love the mission and vision of Javesca Coffee.
Amazingly fresh coffee and the food was very delicious and hit the spot. I would absolutely recommend this spot, especially once the season changes and a nice hot coffee outside is needed!

Wow!! I cannot even begin to express how impressed I was with the food, coffee, and overall polite staff. I tried the TBA and it was savory and packed full of flavor. The chai latte was better then my typical Starbucks chai. My fiancee and I are found our new breakfast spot (⁠ ⁠◜⁠‿⁠◝⁠ ⁠)⁠♡

Best coffee in Steele Creek area! We had cold with hazelnut syrup, and drip coffee. Amazing selection of macarons: had the orange/truffle one, de-li-cious! Will have to try all. Indoor playground is super nice for little ones! Plenty of space to work here or to meet friends!

Spacious, inviting, good selection of food and drinks. Prices are comparable, even a little lower than Starbucks. And, it's the only coffeeshop in the Steele Creek area other than Starbucks. I ordered the Apple Grilled Cheese Panini (highly recommended, btw 😋) and a white chocolate frap with almond milk. Both VERY good!
I'll be back again!

Came here for the grand opening and loved the food, drinks and atmosphere. Excited for normal hours and to meet up with friends or bring some work here on my own.
I had the nitro brew and chicken salad croissants and both were excellent!
